{"type":"message","id":"699bacee","parentId":"ad5a7ff1","timestamp":"2026-03-24T00:24:19.117Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[Mon 2026-03-23 20:24 EDT] [Subagent Context] You are running as a subagent (depth 1/1). Results auto-announce to your requester; do not busy-poll for status.\n\n[Subagent Task]: Research task: Use the `summarize` CLI tool to pull transcripts from competitor YouTube Shorts.\n\n**Tool:** `summarize \"URL\" --youtube auto --extract-only`\n\n**Channels to research (find 5-7 recent Shorts from each):**\n1. @Simplehistory\n2. @HistoryMatters\n3. @HistoryHit\n4. @TimelineChannel\n5. @TheInformationArchive\n6. @ThePineBaron\n7. @EarlyAmerican\n8. @theaihistory22 (AI HISTORY)\n9. @HistoryCuriosityCapsules\n10. @BedtimeHistory\n\n**For each video, capture:**\n1. Video URL\n2. Title\n3. View count (if visible on channel page)\n4. Video length\n5. Full transcript (use summarize tool with --extract-only)\n6. Any notes on hook style, pacing, format\n\n**Important:** Use the summarize tool for transcripts — do NOT use third-party websites or YouTube transcript downloaders. Just use:\n`summarize \"https://youtube.com/shorts/XXXXX\" --youtube auto --extract-only`\n\n**Output:** Save everything to:\n~/Desktop/SecondBrain/Research/CozyColonials_CompetitorAnalysis/YOUTUBE_SHORTS_ANALYSIS.md\n\nFormat cleanly with channel headers and individual video entries."}],"timestamp":1774311859116}}
{"type":"message","id":"3e7d3d62","parentId":"699bacee","timestamp":"2026-03-24T00:24:22.514Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I need to research YouTube Shorts from 10 competitor channels, extract transcripts using the summarize tool, and compile everything into a markdown file. Let me start by reading the summarize skill to understand how to use it properly, then systematically research each channel.","thinkingSignature":"1337f4d8c352e1982501727324c8e4c7696f882b80fae965ccacdd8dd1a2167e"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_h80l8v9a7n3o_1","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/opt/homebrew/lib/node_modules/openclaw/skills/summarize/SKILL.md"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":54,"output":94,"cacheRead":6914,"cacheWrite":9517,"totalTokens":16579,"cost":{"input":0.0000162,"output":0.00011279999999999999,"cacheRead":0.00041484,"cacheWrite":0.003568875,"total":0.004112715}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774311859117,"responseId":"06110cb353cf93667b5bd9f9a3468a7f"}}
{"type":"message","id":"7fe41e60","parentId":"3e7d3d62","timestamp":"2026-03-24T00:24:22.532Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_h80l8v9a7n3o_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"---\nname: summarize\ndescription: Summarize or extract text/transcripts from URLs, podcasts, and local files (great fallback for “transcribe this YouTube/video”).\nhomepage: https://summarize.sh\nmetadata:\n  {\n    \"openclaw\":\n      {\n        \"emoji\": \"🧾\",\n        \"requires\": { \"bins\": [\"summarize\"] },\n        \"install\":\n          [\n            {\n              \"id\": \"brew\",\n              \"kind\": \"brew\",\n              \"formula\": \"steipete/tap/summarize\",\n              \"bins\": [\"summarize\"],\n              \"label\": \"Install summarize (brew)\",\n            },\n          ],\n      },\n  }\n---\n\n# Summarize\n\nFast CLI to summarize URLs, local files, and YouTube links.\n\n## When to use (trigger phrases)\n\nUse this skill immediately when the user asks any of:\n\n- “use summarize.sh”\n- “what’s this link/video about?”\n- “summarize this URL/article”\n- “transcribe this YouTube/video” (best-effort transcript extraction; no `yt-dlp` needed)\n\n## Quick start\n\n```bash\nsummarize \"https://example.com\" --model google/gemini-3-flash-preview\nsummarize \"/path/to/file.pdf\" --model google/gemini-3-flash-preview\nsummarize \"https://youtu.be/dQw4w9WgXcQ\" --youtube auto\n```\n\n## YouTube: summary vs transcript\n\nBest-effort transcript (URLs only):\n\n```bash\nsummarize \"https://youtu.be/dQw4w9WgXcQ\" --youtube auto --extract-only\n```\n\nIf the user asked for a transcript but it’s huge, return a tight summary first, then ask which section/time range to expand.\n\n## Model + keys\n\nSet the API key for your chosen provider:\n\n- OpenAI: `OPENAI_API_KEY`\n- Anthropic: `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY`\n- xAI: `XAI_API_KEY`\n- Google: `GEMINI_API_KEY` (aliases: `GOOGLE_GENERATIVE_AI_API_KEY`, `GOOGLE_API_KEY`)\n\nDefault model is `google/gemini-3-flash-preview` if none is set.\n\n## Useful flags\n\n- `--length short|medium|long|xl|xxl|<chars>`\n- `--max-output-tokens <count>`\n- `--extract-only` (URLs only)\n- `--json` (machine readable)\n- `--firecrawl auto|off|always` (fallback extraction)\n- `--youtube auto` (Apify fallback if `APIFY_API_TOKEN` set)\n\n## Config\n\nOptional config file: `~/.summarize/config.json`\n\n```json\n{ \"model\": \"openai/gpt-5.2\" }\n```\n\nOptional services:\n\n- `FIRECRAWL_API_KEY` for blocked sites\n- `APIFY_API_TOKEN` for YouTube fallback\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774311862527}}
{"type":"message","id":"f55e9d5c","parentId":"7fe41e60","timestamp":"2026-03-24T00:24:27.866Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Good, I understand how to use the summarize tool. Now I need to:\n1. Search for recent Shorts from each channel\n2. Extract transcripts using the summarize tool\n3. Compile everything into a markdown file\n\nLet me start by searching for recent Shorts from each channel. I'll need to find the actual Shorts URLs first, then extract transcripts. Let me begin with web searches for each channel to find their recent Shorts.","thinkingSignature":"ac60c16fd594992956ee10d38d716df6bc9527f5d3bd634f0f1824607b4e6036"},{"type":"text","text":"I'll systematically research each channel, starting by finding their recent YouTube Shorts URLs, then extracting transcripts.\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_8n7db6pggc8s_1","name":"web_search","arguments":{"query":"site:youtube.com @Simplehistory shorts","count":10}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_8n7db6pggc8s_2","name":"web_search","arguments":{"query":"site:youtube.com @HistoryMatters shorts","count":10}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_8n7db6pggc8s_3","name":"web_search","arguments":{"query":"site:youtube.com @HistoryHit shorts","count":10}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_8n7db6pggc8s_4","name":"web_search","arguments":{"query":"site:youtube.com @TimelineChannel shorts","count":10}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_8n7db6pggc8s_5","name":"web_search","arguments":{"query":"site:youtube.com @TheInformationArchive shorts","count":10}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":1098,"output":304,"cacheRead":16095,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":17497,"cost":{"input":0.0003294,"output":0.0003648,"cacheRead":0.0009656999999999999,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0016598999999999997}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774311862532,"responseId":"06110cb6b0b92fd3350f6572f49ea0ae"}}
