{"type":"message","id":"af4c1469","parentId":"254c53cb","timestamp":"2026-03-24T00:26:15.762Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_wlz3xy08js99_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Transcript:\nafter his defeat Napoleon was exiled to\nthe small island of Elba here but why\nthere instead of literally anywhere else\non Earth well the reason why was mostly\nthe Russian Emperor Alexander the first\nwhose Army was one of the first into\nParis since Alexander just wanted to be\nseen as a swell guy he negotiated with\nthe remainder of the French leadership\nthe Mediterranean was close enough to\nkeep an eye on Napoleon and so Alexander\nchose one of the islands there Corsica\nSardinia and Sicily were too large to\ngive to Napoleon and so the tiny island\nof Elba are now ruled by Austria was\nchosen this was agreed by Russia Prussia\nand Austria by the time the rest of the\nAllies got to Paris which annoyed them\nbecause Britain wanted to send Napoleon\nto India as such it was simpler just to\nagree with Russia than to rock the boat\nover a defeated enemy and so off to Elba\nNapoleon went\n\n3.7s · 43s YouTube · 165 words · text via transcript/captionTracks"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":4350,"aggregated":"Transcript:\nafter his defeat Napoleon was exiled to\nthe small island of Elba here but why\nthere instead of literally anywhere else\non Earth well the reason why was mostly\nthe Russian Emperor Alexander the first\nwhose Army was one of the first into\nParis since Alexander just wanted to be\nseen as a swell guy he negotiated with\nthe remainder of the French leadership\nthe Mediterranean was close enough to\nkeep an eye on Napoleon and so Alexander\nchose one of the islands there Corsica\nSardinia and Sicily were too large to\ngive to Napoleon and so the tiny island\nof Elba are now ruled by Austria was\nchosen this was agreed by Russia Prussia\nand Austria by the time the rest of the\nAllies got to Paris which annoyed them\nbecause Britain wanted to send Napoleon\nto India as such it was simpler just to\nagree with Russia than to rock the boat\nover a defeated enemy and so off to Elba\nNapoleon went\n\n3.7s · 43s YouTube · 165 words · text via transcript/captionTracks","cwd":"/Users/bobbygalletta/.openclaw/workspace-yoyos"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774311975760}}
