{"type":"message","id":"1181aa94","parentId":"6c81ce32","timestamp":"2026-03-24T00:29:43.729Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"HistoryCuriosityCapsules has a lot of Shorts. Let me get transcripts from 5-7 of them, focusing on the ones with more views and the ones relevant to CozyColonials niche (Colonial American). Let me select:\n\n1. FZyVeErxq7s - \"The Shocking Beheading of Anne Boleyn\" - 17K views\n2. NM09y8-wUa4 - \"The Battle of Little Bighorn\" - 20K views\n3. UBxnYzsCfDU - \"The Real Saving Private Ryan? The Story of Fritz Niland\" - 5.2K views\n\n\n4. V0JbGFw_r3Q - \"How Mexico Won the Alamo… But Lost the War\" - 3.8K views\n5. 1tMHFP63Szo - \"The Black Panthers Who Changed WWII\" - 3.9K views\n6. X2ZxKBUShLE - \"Colonial America's Election Day: A Time for Parties and Politics\" - 655 views (very relevant to CozyColonials!)\n7. sJXe3-Oxj50 - \"McKinley's Assassination: The Birth of the Secret Service\" - 3.2K views\n\nI've got a solid mix of military history, political figures, and colonial-era content. Now I need to pull the transcripts and then move on to checking out BedtimeHistory.","thinkingSignature":"18586855a0e22c0ea73cfaa84c40e8343a75fe53dbeaf4d1031ce0e80f4fae6b"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_6xu7fzkptk8s_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"summarize \"https://youtube.com/shorts/FZyVeErxq7s\" --youtube auto --extract-only 2>&1 && echo \"---NEXT---\" && summarize \"https://youtube.com/shorts/NM09y8-wUa4\" --youtube auto --extract-only 2>&1 && echo \"---NEXT---\" && summarize \"https://youtube.com/shorts/UBxnYzsCfDU\" --youtube auto --extract-only 2>&1 && echo \"---NEXT---\" && summarize \"https://youtube.com/shorts/V0JbGFw_r3Q\" --youtube auto --extract-only 2>&1 && echo \"---NEXT---\" && summarize \"https://youtube.com/shorts/X2ZxKBUShLE\" --youtube auto --extract-only 2>&1","yieldMs":120000,"timeout":150}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_6xu7fzkptk8s_2","name":"browser","arguments":{"action":"navigate","targetId":"807C31555A855924C511E400A3AF2BF0","url":"https://www.youtube.com/@BedtimeHistory/shorts"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":73936,"output":588,"cacheRead":16095,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":90619,"cost":{"input":0.0221808,"output":0.0007056,"cacheRead":0.0009656999999999999,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0238521}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774312170385,"responseId":"06110dea1ec76719ae0fb52da1781c9b"}}
{"type":"message","id":"adf07ea9","parentId":"1181aa94","timestamp":"2026-03-24T00:30:02.585Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_6xu7fzkptk8s_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Transcript:\nAnne bin the second wife of King Henry\nVI e played a pivotal role in the\nEnglish Reformation their marriage in\n1533 marked a dramatic shift in\nEngland's religious landscape as Queen\nAnne was a key player at court but she\nsoon found herself surrounded by\nenemies by 1536 Henry had his eyes set\non Jane Seymour and Anne's influence\nbegan to wne Anne was arrested on\ncharges of adultery incest and high\ntreason crimes she denied vehemently the\ntrial was a spectacle with many\nbelieving the charges were fabricated to\nremove Anne from Power despite her\ndefense Anne was found guilty and\nsentenced to death on May 19th 1536 Anne\nwas taken to the Tower of London to face\nher\nexecution a French swordsman was brought\nto ensure a swift execution as Henry\nwanted to avoid a botched beheading an's\nfinal words were of Acceptance in prayer\ndisplaying remarkable composure I pray\nGod Save the King and send him long to\nre over you for a gentler nor a more\nmerciful Prince was there\nnever the execution was Swift and Ann's\nlife ended with a single stroke of the\nsword\n\n3.5s · 58s YouTube · 191 words · text via transcript/captionTracks\n---NEXT---\nTranscript:\non June 25th 1876 one of the most famous\nbattles in American history took place\nthe Battle of Little Big Horn the battle\noccurred near the Little Big Horn River\nin Montana territory involving the US\n7eventh Cavalry and an alliance of\nLakota Sue Cheyenne and Dapo tribes\ntensions had been rising for years due\nto broken trees and encroachment on\nNative American lands leaders like\nSitting Bull and Crazy Horse galvanized\ntheir people to resist Lieutenant\nColonel George Armstrong kuster led the\nUS 7th Cavalry in a reckless assault\nunder estimating the strength and\nresolve of the Native American forces\nthe combined Native American forces\nnumbering around 2,000 warriors were\nprepared to defend their way of life\nkuster's troops were quickly overwhelmed\nthe fierce fighting resulted in a\ncomplete annihilation of kuster and his\nimmediate command the US suffered a\ndevastating defeat with over 250\nsoldiers killed including kuster himself\nthe victory at Little Big Horn was a\nsignificant yet temporary Triumph for\nthe Native American tribes\n\n3.2s · 59s YouTube · 168 words · text via transcript/captionTracks\n---NEXT---\nTranscript:\nin the chaos of World War II the story\nof one soldier Fritz Nyland stands out\nas a tale of family sacrifice and\nsurvival Fritz Nyland was an American\nparatrooper in the1st Airborne Division\nknown for its pivotal role in the D-Day\ninvasion Fritz was one of four brothers\nserving in the war his brothers Edward\nPreston and Robert were also in active\ncombat tragically in June 1944 the\nNyland family received devastating news\nEdward was missing an action in the\nBurma theater Preston died on D-Day and\nRobert was killed the day after dday\nthe US war department determined to\nprevent further loss for the Nyland\nordered Fritz to be sent home Fritz\nnyland's Journey back to the United\nStates was an arduous one but he\nreturned safely bringing a glimmer of\nhope to his grieving family Fritz's\nStory of Survival and the military's\nefforts to save him inspired the plot of\nSteven Spielberg's iconic film Saving\nPrivate Ryan though the film takes\nartistic Liberties the core of the story\nremains true the mission to save a\nsoldier after the tragic loss of his\nbrothers\n\n3.6s · 58s YouTube · 186 words · text via transcript/captionTracks\n---NEXT---\nTranscript:\nin 1836 the Battle of the Alamo became a\nsymbol of resistance and sacrifice in\nthe Texas Revolution despite a valiant\ndefense the Texan Rebels were ultimately\noverrun by Mexican forces under General\nSanta Ana the Mexican victory at the\nAlamo was shortlived as it galvanized\nTexan forces and led to the pivotal\nBattle of\nsanino at San jasinto Sam Houston's Army\ndecisively defeated Santa Ana securing\nTexas\nIndependence however tensions between\nthe United States and Mexico soon\nescalated leading to the\nMexican-American war in\n1846 despite early victories Mexico was\noutmatched by the United States Superior\nresources and Military strategy the\nMexican-American War highlighted the\nStark differences in military capability\nand Leadership between the two Nations\nthe war ended in 1848 with the Treaty of\nGuadalupe hialgo forcing Mexico to seed\nvast territories to the United States\n\n3.4s · 57s YouTube · 138 words · text via transcript/captionTracks\n---NEXT---\nTranscript:\never wondered how elections in colonial\nAmerica were\ncelebrated in colonial America election\nday was more than just casting votes it\nwas a massive celebration complete with\nfood drinks and\nfestivities candidates would often\nprovide alcohol and host big parties to\nattract voters these gatherings weren't\njust for fun they were critical for\npoliticians to gain favor this tradition\nwas so ingrained that law sometimes\nrequired them to provide\nRefreshments after casting their votes\ncitizens joined in election parties\nfilled with food drink and\nentertainment Colonial games horse races\nand contests were common making election\nday a festive Community event taverns\nplayed a central role hosting Lively\ndiscussions debates and toasts to\ncandidates and causes what do you think\nmodern elections could learn from these\nearly American traditions please leave a\ncomment\n\n3.2s · 50s YouTube · 132 words · text via transcript/captionTracks"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":18832,"aggregated":"Transcript:\nAnne bin the second wife of King Henry\nVI e played a pivotal role in the\nEnglish Reformation their marriage in\n1533 marked a dramatic shift in\nEngland's religious landscape as Queen\